<body>
<h4> My Role </h4>
<hr>
<p> Subject leader (<i>Fall 2023, PolyU</i>)
<ol>
<li> Deliver 3-hour lectures per week and supervise 3-hour laboratory sessions.</li>
<li> Create lecture materials, laboratory materials, assignments, in-class questions.</li>
<li> Design and mark the mid-term test and final exam papers.</li>
</ol>
</p>

<h3> Course Content </h3>
<hr>
<p> 
<ol>
<li> Basic  switched-modeDC/DC topologies, operation, performance and modeling</li>
<li> Resonant converter and itsmethod of loss reduction.</li>
<li> Switched mode techniques to inverters (DC/AC converters).</li>
<li> Power electronics circuit simulation.</li>
<li> Impact of electromagnetic interference (EMI) and the reduction of EMI using power electronicstechniques.</li>
</ol>
</p>

<h3> Assessment </h3>
<hr>
<p> 
<ol>
<li> Assignment: 10% (home work)</li>
<li> Short test: 15% (Two 30-45 mins in-class short tests)</li>
<li> Lab Report: 15% (1 lab report)</li>
<li> Examination: 60% (One three-hour examination)</li>
</ol>
</p>



